The most reported ancestries in [[2020 United States census|2020]] were:<ref>{{cite web |title=TOTAL POPULATION |url=https://data.census.gov/table?t=-06:-1000E:-3000F:-4000G:-5000K:-7000E:-8000B&g=160XX00US4253944&d=DEC+Detailed+Demographic+and+Housing+Characteristics+File+A |website=data.census.gov |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau}}</ref>
* [[Irish Americans|Irish]] (22.4%)
* [[German Americans|German]] (19.5%)
* [[Lithuanian Americans|Lithuanian]] (17.1%)
* [[Polish Americans|Polish]] (11%)
* [[English Americans|English]] (7.4%)
* [[Italian Americans|Italian]] (6.7%)
* [[Puerto Ricans|Puerto Rican]] (2.8%)
* [[Pennsylvania Germans|Pennsylvania German]] (2.3%)
* [[Dutch Americans|Dutch]] (2.2%)

At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] there were 1,085 people, 477 households, and 300 families residing in the borough. The population density was {{convert|729.85|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. There were 477 housing units at an average density of {{convert|393.5|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of the borough was 91.14% White, 0.55%, and 0.92% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 1.66%.<ref name="GR2" />

Of the 477 households, 21.38% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 43.0% were married couples living together, 11.7% had a female householder with no husband present, and 37.11% were non-families. 33.54% of households were one person, and 16.35% were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.27 and the average family size was 2.84.

In the borough the population was spread out, with 18.71% under the age of 18, 3.78% from 18 to 20, 53.46% from 21 to 61, 5.25% from 62 to 64, and 18.8% 65 or older. The median age was 44.9 years. For every 100 females there were 99.1 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 100 males.

From the 2000 census, the median household income was $27,159 and the median family income was $38,229. Males had a median income of $29,107 versus $20,192 for females. The per capita income for the borough was $17,899. About 6.3% of families and 10.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 17.0% of those under age 18 and 13.3% of those age 65 or over.

In 2000, 20.8% of New Philadelphia residents identified as being of [[Lithuanians|Lithuanian]] heritage. This was the highest percentage of Lithuanian Americans per capita in the country.

